Vintage illustration of a plump, overstuffed filing cabinet with papers and forms bursting from every drawer, gradually transforming into a sleek, slim folder on the right side of the image. The scene shows the metamorphosis mid-process, with loose paper fragments floating away like autumn leaves in a warm breeze. The color palette features muted yellows, burnt oranges, and cream tones reminiscent of 1950s technical manuals. The filing cabinet has an anthropomorphized quality, looking relieved as it sheds weight. Scattered around the base are tiny XML-like brackets and code symbols rendered as decorative flourishes. The background suggests a cozy workshop environment with warm wood tones and soft shadows, evoking the satisfaction of tidying and organizing cherished old tools.
